[2
Date: Sun, 5 Apr 1998 14:14:34 -0600
From: Martin Hugh-Jones <mehj2020@vt8200.vetmed.lsu.edu>

Some odd things about this report ... they seem to have done a very narrow
viral search for the presence of antibodies and then what titre did they
take as "positive"? There are positive titres and then there is infection. A
low titre is interesting but nothing else. A medium-to-high titre is more
indicative of an infection. Also were the "four" clustered, possibly
indicating a primate center with poor hygiene, husbandry, whatever?
